properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 13 at 9:53AM CST until February 14 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Dangerously Cold Temperatures Continue Through Friday
Morning...

* WHAT...For the Wind Chill Warning, dangerously cold wind chills
of 30 to 35 below zero are expected. For the Wind Chill
Advisory, wind chills as low as 20 to 30 below zero are
expected.

* WHERE...North-Central Iowa.

* WHEN...For the Wind Chill Warning, until noon CST today. For
the Wind Chill Advisory, until 10 AM CST Friday.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 to 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Avoid outside activities if possible. When outside, make sure you
wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY... ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM CST FRIDAY
